ter Clown</a> that murders children, Buddy is basically Pennywise from <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/It" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/It">It</a></em> by <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/StephenKing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/StephenKing">Stephen King</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeScream">Eye Scream</a>;<ul><li> A bogle Rio's the eyes out of a mall security guard and plays tennis with them.</li><li> Fool rip's out Bigmouth's eyes and puts them in his own head.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FamilyThemeNaming" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FamilyThemeNaming">Family Theme Naming</a>: The Gundersons are all named after Greek gods.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanConvention" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanConvention">Fan Convention</a>: Amber tracks her oarent to a <em>Dark Places</em> convention.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFerryman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFerryman">The Ferryman</a>: Amber has to pay one to take her from Astaroth's castle to The Blood-dimmed King's palace.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlippingTheBird" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FlippingTheBird">Flipping the Bird</a>: Amber to her father as he's trying to make a deal to work together against Astaroth.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForTheEvulz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForTheEvulz">For the Evulz</a>: Mauk's sole reason for torturing the teenagers in the cabin.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FriendlyNeighbourhoodVampire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FriendlyNeighbourhoodVampire">Friendly Neighbourhood Vampire</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Glen</span> vows to be one, only feeding off criminals. He later takes small amounts of blood off of innocent people when he can't find any criminals.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGenieKnowsJackNicholson" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheGenieKnowsJackNicholson">The Genie Knows Jack Nicholson</a>: Amber wonders why the bogles are immigrating human movies and Axton mentions they watch TV.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlOnGirlIsHot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GirlOnGirlIsHot">Girl-on-Girl Is Hot</a>: A load of men cheer when Amber makes out with a girl in a club.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiveMeBackMyWallet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GiveMeBackMyWallet">Give Me Back My Wallet</a>: Amber chases Clarissa to get her bag back and the two end up becoming friends.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GlamourFailure" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GlamourFailure">Glamour Failure</a>: People possessed by Aaliyah Brewer can be recognised because she always chews her upper lip.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GuileHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GuileHero">Guile Hero</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment">Amber</a>, who <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DidYouJustScamCthulhu" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DidYouJustScamCthulhu">cheats both her parents and The Shining Demon</a>.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HauntedTechnology" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HauntedTechnology">Haunted Technology</a>: Aaliyah Brewer is a ghost that can travel through the internet to phones and computers.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HellHasNewManagement" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HellHasNewManagement">Hell Has New Management</a>: What Amber's parents hope to accomplish in the long run.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AHellOfATime" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AHellOfATime">A Hell of a Time</a>: Though it's mostly torture, a priest Amber meets in Hell says some people occasionally form friendships or fall in love there.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImAHumanitarian" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImAHumanitarian">I'm a Humanitarian</a>: The Gundersons.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InnOfNoReturn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InnOfNoReturn">Inn of No Return</a>: The Catching Z's motel has rooms full of deadly traps and two-way mirrors where the manager watches the antics.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvisibleToAdults" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InvisibleToAdults">Invisible to Adults</a>: Buddy the ghost <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MonsterClown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MonsterClown">Monster Clown</a> can't be seen or felt by anyone over the age of 18. Interestingly, the injuries on his victim's bodies can only be seen by people under 18. To adults it seems like they died of sudden death in their sleep.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustJokingJustification" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustJokingJustification">"Just Joking" Justification</a>;<ul><li> When Amber gets angry with Leon hinting that she and Pixie-cut would pay him and Spencer with sexual favours for directing them to a club, he says they weren't being totally serious.</li><li> In jail, Reggie says his sexual comments were just a joke after Amber grabs him by the throat.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KingIncognito" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KingIncognito">King Incognito</a>: The priest Amber meets in Hell<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> is The Blood-dimmed King in disguise</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KissOfTheVampire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KissOfTheVampire">Kiss of the Vampire</a>: Being turned into a vampire is incredibly erotic. Even if you're straight and the vampire is the same gender.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MarsNeedsWomen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MarsNeedsWomen">Mars Needs Women</a>: The Gundersons want to capture a demon for the purpose of breeding with.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheMenInBlack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheMenInBlack">The Men in Black</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The Foundation of Light is an organisation of ex-soldiers and cops who fight monsters and serial killers.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MonsterClown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MonsterClown">Monster Clown</a>: Simon Cranston/Buddy. He is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy">remarkable similar</a> to Pennywise.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoodWhiplash" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoodWhiplash">Mood Whiplash</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Balthazar's-Arm-Candy turns out to be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroKiller" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroKiller">Betty</a>, who <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KilledOffscreen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KilledOffscreen">kills Warrick, Linda and Ronnie offscreen.</a></span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyGodWhatHaveIDone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyGodWhatHaveIDone">My God, What Have I Done?</a>: Amber after the nightclub scene.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind">No Body Left Behind</a>: The undead serial killers after their <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar">Soul Jars</a> are destroyed.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoTellMotel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoTellMotel">No-Tell Motel</a>: Catching Z's. Turns out to be a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HellHotel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HellHotel">Hell Hotel</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneHeroHoldTheWeaksauce" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneHeroHoldTheWeaksauce">One Hero, Hold the Weaksauce</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Glen</span> claims to have all the strengths of a vampire and none of the weaknesses, he then admits he's lying.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneWingedAngel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneWingedAngel">One-Winged Angel</a>: Astaroth takes a more <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EldritchAbomination" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EldritchAbomination">Eldritch Abomination</a> type form when killing <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Amber's parents.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayAlongPrisoner" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayAlongPrisoner">Play-Along Prisoner</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Astaroth decides to do this with fake chains when Amber tells him her parents want her to deliver him to them.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoweredByAForsakenChild" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoweredByAForsakenChild">Powered by a Forsaken Child</a>: One couple that Amber collects an offering from are strongly implied to have killed their baby. Their <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar">Soul Jar</a> is later shown to be a baby's skull.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedemptionEqualsDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedemptionEqualsDeath">Redemption Equals Death</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Milo get killed at the end.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RemovingTheHeadOrDestroyingTheBrain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RemovingTheHeadOrDestroyingTheBrain">Removing the Head or Destroying the Brain</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Discussed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Discussed">Discussed</a>, then <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Averted" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Averted">averted</a>. Mauk's zombies need to be completely dismembered before they stop moving.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RescuedFromTheUnderworld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RescuedFromTheUnderworld">Rescued from the Underworld</a>: Amber goes to Hell to bring <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Glen's</span> soul back. She promises to take Bigmouth with her for helping but he gets caught by Fool.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShinyNewAustralia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShinyNewAustralia">Shiny New Australia</a>: If Amber's parents manage to take over Hell, they decide to turn her into a Demon and give her a territory similar to what Astaroth has.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SoulJar">Soul Jar</a>: Serial killers that are resurrected by Demons will be invincible unless a particular object they own is destroyed.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSoulless" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSoulless">The Soulless</a>: A persons soul passes straight to Hell when they become a vampire.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpeaksFluentAnimal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpeaksFluentAnimal">Speaks Fluent Animal</a>: Paul Axton sold his soul for the ability to communicate with bogles but he's implied to be able to communicate with any creature.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStarscream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStarscream">The Starscream</a>:<ul><li> The Gundersons were loyal to Amber's parents for years just so they could capture a demon <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreedingSlave" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreedingSlave">Breeding Slave</a> when they got the chance.</li><li> Amber's parents want to be this to the Blood-dimmed King, sucking up to him until they can overthrow him.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SummonMagic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SummonMagic">Summon Magic</a>: Demorial actually appears when summoned instead of taking the summoner to Hell, though he never leaves the circle.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Technopath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Technopath">Technopath</a>: Aaliyah Brewer can travel through the internet.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThroneMadeOfX" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThroneMadeOfX">Throne Made of X</a>: When they take over Astaroth's castle, Bill wants a throne made from the blood of his enemies and Betty wants one made from the blades that slew them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TookALevelInBadass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TookALevelInBadass">Took a Level in Badass</a>: Amber.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainsWantMercy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainsWantMercy">Villains Want Mercy</a>: Amber meets Kirsty and Grant in Hell and they beg her to help them escape.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WackyWaysideTribe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WackyWaysideTribe">Wacky Wayside Tribe</a>: The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImAHumanitarian" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImAHumanitarian">Gundersons</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhaleEgg" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhaleEgg">Whale Egg</a>: Bogles look similar to teddy bears but lay eggs.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatHappenedToTheMouse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatHappenedToTheMouse">What Happened to the Mouse?</a>: The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini">guy from the hotel with the chainsaw</a> never comes up again.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WithGreatPowerComesGreatInsanity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WithGreatPowerComesGreatInsanity">With Great Power Comes Great Insanity</a>: Amber's starting to hallucinate as a side effect of drinking Astaroth's blood and he confirms it's insanity.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WolverineClaws" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WolverineClaws">Wolverine Claws</a>: James couldn't shift into a demon form but could grow claws.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouHaveOutlivedYourUsefulness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouHaveOutlivedYourUsefulness">You Have Outlived Your Usefulness</a>;<ul><li> When Amber's parents <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">think they've eaten Astaroth</span>, the quickly kill their vampire, Stromquist because they've no need for him.</li><li> The Blood-dimmed King <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">kills Astaroth after his game playing had nearly let Amber's parents overthrow him</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKilledMyFather" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouKilledMyFather">You Killed My Father</a>: Byrd shoots <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Milo</span> because he murdered her parents and brother when she was a child.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourCostumeNeedsWork" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YourCostumeNeedsWork">Your Costume Needs Work</a>: When Amber explores Salt Lake City while shifted, most people assume she's in costume.</li></ul></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><p></p><hr>
